### Sensitivity Analysis

| Parameter | Trend |
|---|---|
| Navigation constant N | Median miss decreases N=2→5, modest improvement N=5→6 |
| Target maneuverability | Mild degradation 1g→5g — TPN is relatively robust |
| Seeker noise σ | Minimum near σ=0.2 rad/s — counterintuitive, low-noise regime may excite oscillation |

Optimal N=5 selected for nominal configuration.

### Launch Envelope

Median miss distance below 500m for launch ranges 1-3km, elevation angles 40-65°.
Performance degrades significantly beyond 5km range and below 20° elevation.
Low elevation angle at long range produces extreme altitude error at launch that
the vertical channel cannot overcome within the engagement time.

### Pk vs Launch Range

Pk remains near zero across 0.5-9km range at 50 runs/point with 20m lethal radius.
CEP50 increases monotonically from ~170m at 500m range to ~880m at 9km. Effective
engagement range (CEP50 < lethal radius) not achieved with current guidance — would
require end-game guidance refinement.

### ECM Robustness (100 runs each)

| Condition | CEP50 (m) | Pk (%) |
|---|---|---|
| Nominal σ=0.05 rad/s | 459 m | 0.0 |
| Jammed σ=0.25 rad/s (5x) | 409 m | 0.0 |

ECM has minimal effect on CEP50 — miss distance is dominated by geometry and
maneuver timing, not seeker noise at these noise levels.

