### Data Flow — Single Engagement

```
run_engagement()
│
├── ManeuveringTarget(pos0, heading, speed, max_accel, seed)
│   └── bang-bang lateral accel, RK4 integration, altitude hold
│
├── GuidanceLaw(variant, N, noise_std, accel_limit, tau, seed)
│   └── wraps true_pn() / pure_pn() / augmented_pn()
│
└── Integration loop (while t < t_max):
    │
    ├── r_m, v_m = missile_state[0:3], missile_state[3:6]
    ├── r_t, v_t = target.pos, target.vel
    │
    ├── GuidanceLaw.compute(r_m, r_t, v_m_eff, v_t, a_t, dt)
    │   ├── true_pn() → compute_los_rate() → omega_perp
    │   │              → a_cmd = N * Vc * omega_perp
    │   │              → a_cmd[Z] = P-controller + gravity comp
    │   ├── clip XY to accel_limit, clip Z to 0.5*accel_limit
    │   └── first-order lag → a_achieved
    │
    ├── rk4_step(missile_derivatives, t, state, dt, a_achieved)
    │   └── F_thrust + F_drag + F_gravity + a_lateral → state_dot
    │
    ├── target.step(dt)
    │
    ├── R = norm(r_t - r_m)
    ├── update min_range, cpa_idx
    └── check: hit / ground / seeker lost post-CPA
```

### Data Flow — Monte Carlo

```
monte_carlo.py __main__
│
├── run_monte_carlo(n_runs=500)
│   └── for i in range(n_runs):
│       ├── randomize_params(NOMINAL, rng) → params dict
│       ├── run_engagement(**params) → result dict
│       └── collect miss_distances[i], hit_flags[i]
│
├── plot_miss_histogram(miss_distances, hit_flags)
├── plot_pn_comparison()     — re-runs MC 3x with PPN/TPN/APN
├── plot_launch_envelope()   — sweeps range × elevation angle
├── plot_pk_vs_range()       — sweeps launch range 0.5–9 km
├── plot_sensitivity()       — sweeps N, target_accel, noise_std
└── plot_ecm_comparison()    — nominal vs 5x seeker noise
```

### Key Functions

**`compute_los_rate(r_m, r_t, v_m, v_t)`**
Returns LOS rate vector ω (rad/s), LOS unit vector, range R, and closing
velocity Vc. Core geometry used by all three PN variants.

    ω = cross(los_hat, v_rel) / R
    Vc = -dot(v_rel, los_hat)

**`true_pn(r_m, r_t, v_m, v_t, N, noise_std, ...)`**
Projects ω perpendicular to missile velocity, computes lateral acceleration
command, overrides Z channel with P-controller. Returns `(a_cmd, seeker_valid)`.

**`GuidanceLaw.compute(r_m, r_t, v_m, v_t, a_t, dt)`**
Calls the appropriate PN function, clips XY and Z independently, applies
first-order actuator lag. Returns `(a_achieved, seeker_valid)`.

**`missile_derivatives(t, state, a_lateral)`**
Point mass EOM. Thrust along velocity vector, drag along negative velocity
vector, gravity downward, lateral acceleration added directly. Returns
`state_dot = [vx, vy, vz, ax, ay, az]`.

**`run_engagement(...)`**
Orchestrates the integration loop. Returns a result dict containing
`miss_distance`, `hit`, `t_cpa`, and full history arrays for trajectory
plotting and animation.

### Validation Tests (`test_guidance.py`)

All 8 tests pass. Actual results from last run:

| Test | What it checks | Result |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | LOS geometry — correct range, unit vector components | Range 500.0m, hat [0.6, 0.8, 0.0] ✓ |
| 2 | Closing velocity — positive closing, negative diverging | Vc=300.0 m/s, div=-300.0 m/s ✓ |
| 3 | PPN zero command on collision course (ω=0) | 0.0000 m/s² ✓ |
| 4 | TPN seeker FOV — invalid for rear target, valid for forward | Both cases correct ✓ |
| 5 | APN lateral command ≥ TPN when target is accelerating | TPN=0.00, APN=60.00 m/s² ✓ |
| 6 | First-order lag convergence within 5s | Converged at 0.51s ✓ |
| 7 | Stationary target miss distance < 350m | 156.8m ✓ |
| 8 | TPN median miss ≤ 1.5× PPN median (20 runs) | TPN=319.6m, PPN=829.8m (2.6× improvement) ✓ |

**Test 5 note:** TPN lateral command is 0.00 m/s² because the test geometry places
missile and target at the same altitude on a head-on course — omega_perp is zero,
so TPN produces no lateral command. APN correctly adds the target acceleration
compensation term regardless. Not a bug — degenerate geometry for the TPN lateral
channel.

**Test 7 note:** 156.8m miss on a noiseless stationary target is driven entirely
by the altitude controller overshooting from 10m launch altitude to 587m before
correcting. Passes the <350m threshold. A proper 3D TPN implementation without
the decoupled vertical channel would achieve near-zero miss on this case.

